and naturally I covered for you.

16:15.374 --> 16:18.720
You need to consider a change
before you kill any more patients.

16:18.730 --> 16:19.802
How dare you?

16:19.812 --> 16:23.512
Go be one of those celebrity
TV doctors. You look the part.

16:23.522 --> 16:26.231
Make a lot of money, wear nice clothes.

16:26.241 --> 16:29.013
- You'd be great at it.
- You watch yourself, Conrad.

16:30.053 --> 16:32.171
You know, I'm remembering
a pretty, young resident

16:32.172 --> 16:35.375
that reported a fatal chemo
overdose a couple years back.

16:35.385 --> 16:37.120
That good deed... that led to a lawsuit

16:37.130 --> 16:39.943
that cost the hospital millions.

16:39.953 --> 16:42.459
You tell me, Conrad, where is she today?

16:42.469 --> 16:44.754
WOMAN [ON MONITOR]:
...with cutting-edge research.

16:44.755 --> 16:46.421
At this moment,
our patients are involved

16:46.422 --> 16:48.213
in over 100...

16:48.214 --> 16:49.797
Not here.

16:53.692 --> 16:56.088
♪ Gonna be here all my life ♪

16:56.089 --> 16:58.963
♪ But I don't know what else to do... ♪

16:58.964 --> 17:01.609
How'd you get that cheeseburger, Chad?

17:01.619 --> 17:03.420
Delivery app.

17:03.421 --> 17:06.257
It looks like you haven't
been following your diet.

17:06.267 --> 17:07.872
Diets don't work.

17:07.882 --> 17:10.296
Have you been taking your insulin?

17:10.297 --> 17:12.290
I don't want a lecture, Nic.

17:12.300 --> 17:15.755
I'm here 'cause my toe's killing me.

17:15.765 --> 17:17.463
[GAGS]

17:19.348 --> 17:21.547
Severe gangrene.

17:22.214 --> 17:24.131
♪ All I know ♪

17:25.422 --> 17:28.406
♪ Hear me on the radio ♪

17:28.415 --> 17:31.420
♪ But I keep thinking ♪
♪ the time will go... ♪

17:32.506 --> 17:35.079
The toe was already dead.
I just touched it.

17:35.886 --> 17:38.109
- He broke my toe!
- His toe fell off.

17:38.119 --> 17:40.754
Chad, buddy, we are amputating
the whole foot.

17:40.755 --> 17:43.457
You knew this was coming. Devon.

17:43.467 --> 17:45.757
What do you think they got for dessert?

17:47.641 --> 17:49.412
You can't keep me here!

17:49.422 --> 17:51.858
- IRVING: You need to settle down.
- CARA: Calm down.

17:51.868 --> 17:56.058
New admission. 21-year-old girl,
history of IV drug use.

17:56.068 --> 17:57.521
Likely endo.

17:57.531 --> 18:00.132
She was trying to steal Dilaudid.
Now she wants to leave AMA.

18:00.142 --> 18:03.361
- She's been spiking fever, vomiting.
- SISTER: She's using again.

18:03.368 --> 18:05.051
She took all my money
and spent it on oxy.

18:05.061 --> 18:06.587
- [YELLING]
- Oy, listen to me.

18:06.588 --> 18:08.683
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Please, stop.

18:08.693 --> 18:12.587
Hey, hey, hey. See these?
See these? These are Osler's nodes

18:12.588 --> 18:14.358
caused by bacteria swarming
in your blood

18:14.365 --> 18:16.682
and moving throughout your body.
Classic for endocarditis,

18:16.689 --> 18:18.792
an infection of the heart valve.

18:18.802 --> 18:20.838
Happens to drug users all the time.

18:21.783 --> 18:25.462
If you walk out of here without any
antibiotics, this will kill you.

18:25.463 --> 18:28.245
If you give us a chance,
we can save your life.

18:29.732 --> 18:34.583
I'll stay if you give me
three milligrams of Dilaudid.

18:34.904 --> 18:36.983
Two.

18:37.608 --> 18:42.560
If you calm down and
you get back in bed right now.

18:51.129 --> 18:52.421
Chloe, baby!

18:53.039 --> 18:54.546
- Get a crash cart.
- Chloe, baby!

18:54.547 --> 18:57.420
- I'm not getting a pulse.
- Code Blue in ED alpha!

18:57.421 --> 18:59.230
- Get them out of here.
- No, no!

18:59.237 --> 19:01.110
- Baby, no! No!
- You need to give them space.

19:01.117 --> 19:03.004
Start compressions.
You're running the code.

19:03.005 --> 19:05.213
- I've never run a code.
- Do you want an amp of bicarb?

19:05.214 --> 19:06.420
He's in charge.

19:06.421 --> 19:08.089
IRVING: Page Anesthesia.

19:10.414 --> 19:13.204
What is the first question
you ask in a code?

19:14.842 --> 19:16.235
Rhythm.

19:16.245 --> 19:18.324
What's her rhythm?

19:18.334 --> 19:20.171
P.E.A.

19:20.172 --> 19:22.127
- Should we shock?
- No, we can't.

19:22.137 --> 19:25.046
Her rhythm's not shockable. Get me
one of epi. Make those compressions

19:25.047 --> 19:27.459
harder and faster. Prepare to intubate.

19:28.381 --> 19:29.422
[LIGHTLY GRUNTING]

19:36.679 --> 19:38.849
It's been 24 minutes.
It's time to call the code.

19:38.859 --> 19:40.420
No!

19:40.421 --> 19:42.420
This is my code. You gave me this code.

19:44.310 --> 19:46.607
She's 21 years old.

19:46.617 --> 19:48.629
Harder, man.
You need to feel the ribs crack.

19:48.630 --> 19:51.255
[IRVING GRUNTING]

19:52.236 --> 19:53.589
That's enough.

19:53.599 --> 19:55.262
No. Move.

19:57.121 --> 19:58.838
I'm not giving up.

19:58.839 --> 20:00.677
[HEART MONITOR FLATLINING]

20:00.687 --> 20:02.462
I said that's enough.

20:17.636 --> 20:19.630
We got a pulse.

20:21.448 --> 20:23.501
You saved her life.

20:32.712 --> 20:37.021
Her end tidal CO2 was less
than 15 for the entire code.

20:37.031 --> 20:39.993
- That doesn't necessarily mean that...
- Yes. Yes, it does.

20:40.003 --> 20:42.932
She's been without oxygen
to her brain for 26 minutes.

20:42.942 --> 20:46.779
Congratulations, you got her heart
beating again, but she's brain-dead.

21:03.477 --> 21:06.171
CONRAD: You came in here all
bright-eyed and bushy-tailed,

21:06.181 --> 21:08.420
ready to save lives, but today
you didn't save a life.

21:08.421 --> 21:12.932
You saved a brain stem
because you didn't listen to me.

21:12.942 --> 21:17.046
Now the repercussions on Chloe's
family will be catastrophic.

21:18.553 --> 21:20.420
There's no way they'll accept this.

21:20.421 --> 21:22.760
Chloe looks alive.
They'll think she can wake up.

21:22.770 --> 21:26.571
So they will hover over her,
tend to her for days,

21:26.578 --> 21:28.730
weeks, maybe years,
waiting for a miracle to happen

21:28.740 --> 21:30.838
that's utterly impossible.

21:33.071 --> 21:35.683
What was rule one, Devon?

21:36.511 --> 21:38.690
Do whatever you tell me to do.

21:38.700 --> 21:40.420
No questions asked.

21:40.421 --> 21:42.290
All we want to do is help our patients,

21:42.300 --> 21:44.420
but what they don't teach us
in medical school

21:44.421 --> 21:46.956
is there are so many ways to do harm.

22:08.471 --> 22:12.373
As you can see,
the Titian is an amazing piece

22:12.383 --> 22:13.947
of medical technology.

22:13.957 --> 22:17.537
We've nicknamed it the "Hand of God"

22:17.547 --> 22:21.669
because it does what no
human hands could accomplish.

22:21.679 --> 22:24.196
- Even yours?
- [LAUGHTER]

22:24.206 --> 22:26.213
Yeah, even mine.

22:26.214 --> 22:27.420
[BELL CHUCKLES]

22:27.421 --> 22:30.745
BELL: The finest surgeon in the world

22:30.755 --> 22:33.069
would benefit from the Titian.

22:33.079 --> 22:34.838
It's capable

22:34.839 --> 22:39.296
of movements that are incredibly
steady and precise,

22:39.297 --> 22:42.349
virtually eliminating human error.

22:43.364 --> 22:45.830
RENATA: Chastain Park Memorial

22:45.840 --> 22:48.542
is the first hospital in the country

22:48.552 --> 22:51.086
to have this miraculous machine,

22:51.096 --> 22:53.680
thanks to Dr. Bell, who spearheaded

22:53.690 --> 22:55.420
this fund-raising campaign,

22:55.421 --> 22:58.624
and, of course, to you,
our very generous donors.

22:58.634 --> 22:59.672
Thank you.

23:03.765 --> 23:08.540
CONRAD: "Serious complications may
occur, up to and including death.

23:09.385 --> 23:12.180
Individual surgical results may vary."

23:12.190 --> 23:15.963
I've trained for months to do this.
Results will not vary.

23:15.964 --> 23:18.408
CONRAD: Until Bell gets his hands on it.

23:18.418 --> 23:21.879
- Over my dead body.
- I'm sure HODAD could manage that.

23:21.880 --> 23:23.587
I heard a nurse call him HODAD.

23:23.588 --> 23:25.221
What does it stand for?

23:25.231 --> 23:29.022
Hands of Death and Destruction.

23:29.032 --> 23:31.088
You're kidding.
Does that mean everyone knows

23:31.089 --> 23:32.996
about his complication rate?

23:33.006 --> 23:35.276
CONRAD: All the nurses,
some of the doctors.

23:35.283 --> 23:38.074
The ones who pay attention.

23:40.145 --> 23:41.411
Poetry.

23:41.421 --> 23:44.852
But none of the patients.
They're clueless.

23:45.241 --> 23:48.915
You've got the best hands
in the business,

23:48.925 --> 23:52.546
but he's still the most requested
surgeon in the hospital.

23:52.547 --> 23:54.462
Have you seen his reviews online?

23:54.463 --> 23:58.796
- He has got five stars.
- [MINA CHUCKLES]

23:58.797 --> 24:02.208
Top patient review: "McDreamy is real."

24:02.218 --> 24:05.428
- You want to hear yours?
- Don't care.

24:05.438 --> 24:08.024
You got one star.
"Steer clear of Dr. Okafor.

24:08.034 --> 24:11.597
She told me my uterus sucked."

24:11.607 --> 24:13.534
It did suck.

24:16.382 --> 24:18.941
I just had hernia surgery with Dr. Bell.

24:18.951 --> 24:20.547
The man has magic hands.

24:24.639 --> 24:26.759
WOMAN [OVER P.A.]:
Dr. Flores, dial 182...

24:26.769 --> 24:27.828
BELL: Hey.

24:27.838 --> 24:30.329
Randolph, I'm so glad you're here.

24:31.327 --> 24:33.411
Where else would I be?

24:34.107 --> 24:36.004
You better finish up
those smoked oysters.

24:36.005 --> 24:37.470
There's no food after midnight.

24:37.480 --> 24:39.171
All right. They're absolutely delicious.

24:39.172 --> 24:41.711
This whole VIP floor is spectacular.

24:41.721 --> 24:43.629
It's nothing more than
you deserve, my friend.

24:44.983 --> 24:46.963
If it hadn't been
for your generous donation,

24:46.964 --> 24:49.801
there would be no new cancer wing.

24:49.811 --> 24:52.176
- Well...
- So...

24:52.186 --> 24:55.186
I hear you're gonna be the first patient
to benefit from the Titian.

24:55.196 --> 24:56.885
Yeah, it's quite the honor.

24:56.895 --> 24:59.452
I hear the damn thing
practically operates itself.

24:59.462 --> 25:02.097
Have you met your surgeon yet,
Dr. Okafor?

25:02.107 --> 25:03.796
Nope, not yet.

25:03.797 --> 25:05.537
She's Nigerian.

25:05.547 --> 25:07.420
Mm-hmm.

25:07.421 --> 25:09.462
Yeah, here on a visa.

25:09.463 --> 25:11.004
Very promising young resident.

25:11.005 --> 25:12.358
[SIGHS]

25:12.368 --> 25:13.963
What do you mean, "young resident"?

25:13.973 --> 25:15.880
Well, second year, I believe.

25:15.890 --> 25:19.201
Randolph, I spoke directly to the CEO...

25:19.211 --> 25:21.255
I mentioned you... but she told me

25:21.256 --> 25:23.420
that Dr. Okafor was the best

25:23.421 --> 25:26.122
possible person to remove
my prostate with the Titian.

25:26.132 --> 25:29.046
- She'll be fine, I'm fairly certain.
- I want you.

25:29.047 --> 25:30.587
You're the chief of surgery.

25:30.588 --> 25:32.004
Don't you think I deserve the best?

25:32.005 --> 25:33.629
Yes.

25:34.406 --> 25:36.004
And I'll make sure you get it.

25:37.127 --> 25:38.420
Thank you.

25:41.259 --> 25:43.514
Lisa brought this back to you, baby,

25:43.524 --> 25:44.879
your honey bunny.

25:44.880 --> 25:47.503
I'm so happy you're with us again.

25:47.513 --> 25:49.420
I'll be right back, my darling.

25:49.421 --> 25:51.420
Dr. Pravesh,

25:51.421 --> 25:54.420
I never thanked you
for saving my daughter's life.

25:56.065 --> 25:57.462
Thank you.

25:57.463 --> 25:59.963
You're wonderful.

26:00.383 --> 26:02.935
I'll be in the cafeteria
if she wakes up.

26:03.421 --> 26:04.755
[MONITOR BEEPING]

26:16.820 --> 26:18.088
You okay?

26:18.840 --> 26:21.282
Nothing like this has ever
happened to me before.

26:21.292 --> 26:22.963
They'll do an investigation, right?

26:22.964 --> 26:26.657
Are you kidding me? The hospital
will probably give you a medal.

26:26.667 --> 26:30.420
Every day Chloe's in the ICU,
they bill thousands of dollars.

26:30.421 --> 26:32.046
It's a huge payday for them.

26:33.275 --> 26:36.502
Medicine isn't practiced
by saints, Devon.

26:36.512 --> 26:38.213
It's a business.

26:39.005 --> 26:42.823
Yeah, but this, all this,
just isn't what I imagined.

26:42.833 --> 26:44.667
Then you're lucky.

26:45.782 --> 26:49.825
When I was 13, my mom went in
for her routine physical.

26:49.835 --> 26:52.538
They did some tests, and they...

26:52.548 --> 26:56.578
they found something small on her lung.

26:56.588 --> 26:59.147
So they cracked her chest,

26:59.157 --> 27:01.530
and her lung collapsed.

27:01.540 --> 27:05.088
She got pneumonia, and five days later,
she was dead.

27:05.089 --> 27:07.371
She was 38 years old.

27:09.179 --> 27:10.620
I'm so sorry.

27:11.486 --> 27:14.704
This happens all the time, Devon.

27:14.714 --> 27:17.299
Medical error is
the third-leading cause of death

27:17.309 --> 27:21.203
in the United States
after cancer and heart disease.

27:21.213 --> 27:24.217
They don't want us talking about that.

27:24.227 --> 27:27.665
But you still show up here every day.

27:27.675 --> 27:30.572
'Cause it's personal to me.

27:30.582 --> 27:32.794
And there are still plenty of good

27:32.804 --> 27:36.987
doctors and nurses
trying to do the right thing.

27:38.475 --> 27:41.677
I'm just trying to be one of 'em.

27:46.241 --> 27:47.662
Lily.

27:48.666 --> 27:50.820
You look like you're feeling better.

27:50.830 --> 27:54.124
Yeah, yeah. Conrad's a miracle worker.

27:54.134 --> 27:57.463
Well, good. Let's get you back
in bed. You need to stay warm.

28:01.038 --> 28:02.296
Where's your fiancé?

28:02.297 --> 28:05.287
Oh, he... he left a few hours ago.

28:05.297 --> 28:06.671
I was still in the ER.

28:06.672 --> 28:10.172
I bet he's just exhausted.
He'll be back tomorrow, I'm sure.

28:10.182 --> 28:12.210
No, he won't.

28:13.224 --> 28:16.722
I got diagnosed a month after
I got engaged.

28:17.720 --> 28:20.411
It's not his fault.
He didn't sign up for cancer.

28:22.462 --> 28:25.866
I mean, maybe if I just
let him go sooner...

28:25.876 --> 28:28.469
I was selfish.

28:28.479 --> 28:30.004
Didn't want to die alone.

28:30.005 --> 28:31.755
[PAGER BEEPS, VIBRATES]

28:34.945 --> 28:37.243
Do you have to go right away?

28:39.043 --> 28:40.767
No.

28:40.777 --> 28:43.370
No. We can talk.

28:43.952 --> 28:45.838
[SIGHS]

28:47.232 --> 28:48.902
[INDISTINCT VOICE OVER P.A.]

28:49.911 --> 28:51.901
[PAGER BUZZING, BEEPING]

28:56.131 --> 28:58.736
[BUZZING, BEEPING]

29:02.156 --> 29:03.900
[BUZZING, BEEPING]

29:03.901 --> 29:06.900
Come on, man.

29:08.038 --> 29:09.235
[BUZZING, BEEPING]

29:09.444 --> 29:12.559
- [ALARM SOUNDING]
- NIC: Status?

29:12.569 --> 29:14.781
We pushed adenosine
six milligrams, then 12.

29:14.791 --> 29:17.443
- She's still tach'ing away at 180.
- Try verapamil.

29:17.444 --> 29:20.484
WOMAN: That won't work, Dr. Bell,
she's gonna have a heart attack.

29:20.485 --> 29:23.900
- [ALARM SOUNDING]
- [WHISTLING]

29:23.901 --> 29:26.319
[ALARM CONTINUES SOUNDING]

29:26.595 --> 29:29.777
I think her heart's had
enough AV blockade.

29:31.277 --> 29:32.976
[GASPS LOUDLY]

29:33.449 --> 29:36.736
[ALARM SOUNDING]

29:42.381 --> 29:44.152
[SIGHS]

29:46.387 --> 29:48.246
Oh. [GASPS]

29:48.901 --> 29:50.526
[INHALES AND EXHALES SHARPLY]

29:51.677 --> 29:54.701
- [ALARM STOPS, BEEPING]
- Normal rhythm. Her heartbeat is back.

29:54.711 --> 29:55.894
BELL: Ice water stimulus.

29:55.904 --> 29:59.053
Prompts vagal tone,
restores normal rhythm in SVT.

29:59.063 --> 30:02.026
Called the Diver's Reflex.
That was my next step.

30:02.027 --> 30:04.276
Two in one day would have been
a bit excessive.

30:04.277 --> 30:07.359
[INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT OVER P.A.]

30:07.360 --> 30:09.318
Tightening the bolt.

30:10.049 --> 30:12.860
You saved my life, Dr. Bell.

30:12.861 --> 30:14.900
Thank you so much.

30:14.901 --> 30:17.068
- Nothing to it.
- [BEEPING CONTINUES]

30:19.766 --> 30:22.031
I don't have time to give
updates on how the surgeries

30:22.041 --> 30:23.953
went one by one. Are the
families all assembled?

30:23.960 --> 30:26.165
Dr. Okafor, you have to talk
to them each individually.

30:26.175 --> 30:28.900
- There are rules about this.
- I get it.

30:28.901 --> 30:30.900
[INDISTINCT VOICE OVER P.A.,
CROWD CHATTER]

30:30.901 --> 30:33.322
Luis is doing fine. He's in recovery.

30:33.332 --> 30:34.945
- Oh.
- Oh.

30:35.901 --> 30:38.290
Raj is in the ICU. It's touch and go.

30:38.300 --> 30:40.142
- Oh.
- Oh.

30:40.152 --> 30:41.959
Prescott's dead. [SNIFFLES]

30:41.969 --> 30:44.693
What? Huh?

30:44.694 --> 30:47.736
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

30:49.826 --> 30:51.684
Dr. Okafor! A word.

30:51.694 --> 30:53.334
Sorry, I'm on my way out. I need to rest

30:53.344 --> 30:55.472
for the first robot
prostatectomy tomorrow morning.

30:55.482 --> 30:58.298
Well, that's actually why I'm here.
The patient has requested

30:58.308 --> 31:01.427
- a last-minute change in the lineup.
- The lineup?

31:01.437 --> 31:04.581
Lyle's always been my patient.
He's asked me to step in.

31:04.591 --> 31:06.846
Does he have a death wish?

31:08.435 --> 31:11.281
I hear you're applying for an O-1 visa.

31:11.291 --> 31:14.654
You'll need a letter of
recommendation from your supervisor.

31:14.664 --> 31:16.421
- I believe that'd be me.
- Dr. Bell,

31:16.431 --> 31:18.900
you have never touched the Titian.

31:18.901 --> 31:21.776
It takes many hours of practice
to be proficient.

31:21.777 --> 31:23.900
You cannot do that surgery.

31:23.901 --> 31:25.894
As in, it's literally impossible.

31:25.904 --> 31:28.067
You have no idea what's possible

31:28.068 --> 31:29.959
for a surgeon with my experience
and expertise.

31:29.969 --> 31:32.359
The surgery is first thing
tomorrow morning.

31:32.369 --> 31:35.151
There isn't enough time
to bring you up to speed.

31:35.152 --> 31:37.651
I have to draw a line here.
This can't happen.

31:37.652 --> 31:40.243
It's too risky for you
and for the patient.

31:40.253 --> 31:42.900
Oh, then, I'm afraid
you'll be heading back to Abuja.

31:42.901 --> 31:46.581
And as you know, immigration to the
States has become quite difficult.

31:46.591 --> 31:48.900
We're shutting our doors.

31:48.901 --> 31:51.236
Given the political unrest
and the quality

31:51.246 --> 31:53.097
of health care available in Nigeria,

31:53.107 --> 31:55.901
you might want to reconsider.

31:56.561 --> 31:59.502
If I help you, you'll get your visa.
If I don't, you won't.

32:00.910 --> 32:03.402
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

32:03.412 --> 32:04.978
Your call.

32:06.652 --> 32:09.767
Start with a simple maneuver.

32:10.666 --> 32:14.289
Four-millimeter incision
on the ventral surface.

32:14.299 --> 32:17.319
[WHIRRING]

32:24.297 --> 32:26.900
Slow and steady.

32:26.901 --> 32:29.360
I've got it.

32:29.569 --> 32:30.736
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

32:33.880 --> 32:35.527
What the hell's wrong with the machine?

32:36.897 --> 32:38.747
It would be better,

32:39.229 --> 32:41.822
for everyone, if I do this.

32:41.832 --> 32:44.325
No. The patient asked for me.

32:44.335 --> 32:46.150
I'm always there for my patients.

32:48.812 --> 32:53.277
Just put that plum back on the table,
and let's get on with it.

32:54.406 --> 32:56.249
Round 11.

33:02.447 --> 33:05.359
Oh, for crying out loud!

33:05.360 --> 33:07.068
[SNORING]

33:17.943 --> 33:21.360
[SNORING STOPS]

33:23.844 --> 33:26.430
[SNORING]

33:28.915 --> 33:30.469
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

33:31.819 --> 33:33.152
[EXHALES]

33:51.995 --> 33:54.225
This is a new low even for you.

33:56.499 --> 33:59.041
Is your pride really worth more
than the life of a patient?

33:59.051 --> 34:00.620
Get out.

34:03.172 --> 34:05.961
I can't stop this train wreck,
so I just wanted to let you know,

34:05.971 --> 34:08.318
I've arranged for a very wide audience.

34:08.319 --> 34:09.713
What are you talking about?

34:09.723 --> 34:12.568
The hospital's gonna stream
the robotic surgery live.

34:12.569 --> 34:15.775
Not just to the donors
who are watching here,

34:15.777 --> 34:18.150
but to thousands of viewers online.

34:18.152 --> 34:20.650
Unless, of course,
you want to step aside.

34:21.476 --> 34:22.719
[EXHALES]

34:22.728 --> 34:24.487
[CHUCKLES] Idiot.

34:24.496 --> 34:26.768
I'll do no such thing.

34:26.777 --> 34:29.900
The more witnesses the better.

34:29.900 --> 34:34.382
This is going to be
a flawless presentation.

34:52.300 --> 34:54.913
- [BEEPING]
- Do you think you can sleep?

34:54.933 --> 34:57.014
Uh, yeah, I think so.

34:58.166 --> 35:00.306
Hey, can I ask you something?

35:00.307 --> 35:02.431
Of course.

35:02.432 --> 35:04.926
What are my odds?

35:04.936 --> 35:08.399
I mean, is there a chance
I can survive this?

35:08.409 --> 35:12.599
I looked at your chart, and
you're on an intense protocol.

35:12.609 --> 35:14.972
The next few months will be rough,

35:14.973 --> 35:17.516
but you can beat this.

35:18.973 --> 35:20.182
[MONITOR BUZZING]

35:21.786 --> 35:23.645
How are you feeling, Lily?

35:23.655 --> 35:25.361
A bit weak all of a sudden.

35:25.371 --> 35:29.098
Your blood pressure is low. 80/40.
It was 120/90 a minute ago.

35:29.099 --> 35:32.261
Lily. Lily! Lily.

35:32.271 --> 35:34.002
Lily!

35:36.410 --> 35:38.134
Where's Conrad?

35:38.144 --> 35:41.202
- He's in the ER. Why? What's wrong?
- Lily's BP is 70/38 and dropping.

35:41.212 --> 35:43.556
Can we please get rapid response now?

35:43.557 --> 35:47.092
Get a CBC, CMP, LFTs, lactate.
Is the IV wide open?

35:47.102 --> 35:49.056
Systolic's fluctuating,
but it's not good.

35:49.063 --> 35:50.836
We're three liters in already.
It's sepsis.

35:50.846 --> 35:52.686
You want to give norepi peripherally?

35:52.696 --> 35:54.545
No. Get a central line.

35:54.555 --> 35:57.502
No. You've never done one.
We wait for Conrad.

35:57.512 --> 35:59.390
We can't. She'll die.

35:59.391 --> 36:01.407
NIC: Prepare the iodine swabs.

36:01.417 --> 36:04.456
We need norepi and vaso on
the table. Get pharm here now.

36:04.466 --> 36:06.181
I want 12 leads on her at all times.

36:06.182 --> 36:08.349
Call for an ultrasound as backup.

36:12.528 --> 36:14.224
Scalpel.

36:15.444 --> 36:16.914
Scalpel.

36:20.320 --> 36:22.849
NIC: Have respiratory on page, please.

36:27.562 --> 36:30.755
Oh, good. Her pressure's crashing.
We need a central line now.

36:30.765 --> 36:32.378
I can see that.

36:33.190 --> 36:34.422
Go on.

36:35.236 --> 36:36.789
- Do it.
- Conrad, seriously...

36:36.796 --> 36:39.023
- You heard me.
- She's right. You should do it, not me.

36:39.030 --> 36:40.445
Then why are you here?

36:40.455 --> 36:42.963
Premed, med school, MCATs.

36:42.973 --> 36:45.135
Was that just for fun?

36:45.145 --> 36:48.750
Come on. Be a doctor,
or go be something else.

36:48.760 --> 36:51.598
[PANTING]

36:51.599 --> 36:55.377
NIC: Her stats are slipping.
Pressure's 70/38 and dropping fast.

37:18.489 --> 37:19.964
Okay.

37:20.349 --> 37:21.684
Keep going.

37:21.694 --> 37:23.973
So far, you haven't killed her.

37:26.695 --> 37:30.134
Start at five micrograms.
Titrate up as needed.

37:30.144 --> 37:31.444
Don't look at him.

37:31.454 --> 37:32.729
I'm right, and you know it.

37:33.717 --> 37:34.972
What next?

37:35.526 --> 37:37.309
When her pressure levels out,

37:37.319 --> 37:40.274
wean her off the norepi
and then drown her in fluids.

37:41.171 --> 37:44.948
Congratulations.
We just busted your cherry.

37:49.973 --> 37:53.099
[EXHALES]

37:59.247 --> 38:02.972
BELL: We are moments away from the
maiden voyage of our new Titian.

38:02.973 --> 38:05.223
And after having spent
considerable time working

38:05.224 --> 38:07.640
with it, I can definitively say

38:07.641 --> 38:10.983
this is a miraculous machine.

38:10.993 --> 38:14.551
And we expect it to be particularly
useful for radical prostatectomies,

38:14.561 --> 38:16.557
which is what we're doing today.

38:24.307 --> 38:27.724
[SOFT WHIRRING]

38:34.554 --> 38:36.564
[SIGHS] Tell me this isn't happening.

38:36.574 --> 38:39.751
Oh, this is happening.
The man is insane.

38:39.761 --> 38:41.973
Only upside is
this should be a career-ender.

38:45.337 --> 38:47.374
[SIGHS] I can't watch.

38:47.384 --> 38:48.514
I can't look away.

38:48.524 --> 38:52.147
BELL: The prostate has
to be carefully peeled

38:52.157 --> 38:53.390
off the bladder.

38:53.391 --> 38:55.840
The risk of rupture and bleeding is high

38:55.850 --> 38:57.974
in unskilled hands.

39:01.960 --> 39:03.974
How is this possible?

39:09.962 --> 39:11.390
BELL: As you can see, the robotic

39:11.391 --> 39:14.414
instruments are smaller
than your fingernails.

39:14.424 --> 39:16.556
But that blade

39:16.557 --> 39:19.214
is sharper than a #11.

39:20.661 --> 39:26.466
This represents the union of human
ingenuity and cutting-edge technology.

39:28.173 --> 39:31.248
Man and machine are melded,

39:31.258 --> 39:33.049
working as one.

39:50.103 --> 39:52.740
[STEADY BEEPING]

39:57.869 --> 39:59.848
Where's Chloe's family?

40:00.903 --> 40:02.556
They just left for the first time.

40:04.410 --> 40:07.148
The mom was sleeping in there
in case she woke up.

40:14.356 --> 40:16.515
You're done.

40:17.002 --> 40:19.015
You can go home.

40:30.227 --> 40:31.798
Hey!

40:33.193 --> 40:35.931
I want to show you something.

40:40.444 --> 40:43.721
Annabeth. Five. She had cancer.

40:43.731 --> 40:46.569
I was a first year, just like you.

40:46.579 --> 40:49.721
I gave her too much potassium.

40:49.731 --> 40:51.859
She died.

40:51.869 --> 40:53.973
From me, not the cancer.

40:56.196 --> 40:58.637
If it were easy,
everyone would be a doctor,

40:58.647 --> 41:02.506
because this is the best job in
the world. Despite everything.

41:03.802 --> 41:05.516
Because of everything.

41:11.956 --> 41:13.972
I'll see you tomorrow.

